<div class=3D"entry-content">
<p>
Let <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/ChineseRemai=
nderTheorem/Inline1.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;m=
ax-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"7" height=3D"21" alt=3D"r">
 and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/ChineseRema=
inderTheorem/Inline2.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;=
max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"7" height=3D"21" alt=3D"s">
 be <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/PositiveInteger.html">positive=
 integers</a> which are <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Relatively=
Prime.html">relatively
 prime</a> and let <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equatio=
ns/ChineseRemainderTheorem/Inline3.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"ma=
x-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" alt=3D=
"a"> and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Chinese=
RemainderTheorem/Inline4.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:1=
00%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" alt=3D"b"> be an=
y two <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Integer.html">integers</a>. =
Then there
 is an <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Integer.html">integer</a> <=
img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/ChineseRemainderT=
heorem/Inline5.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-wi=
dth:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"14" height=3D"21" alt=3D"N"> such that
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
