redequation" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D=
"97" height=3D"20" alt=3D" N=3Db (mod s). "></td><td align=3D"right" width=
=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn2" class=3D"eqnum">
(2)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
Moreover, <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Chines=
eRemainderTheorem/Inline6.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:=
100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"14" height=3D"21" alt=3D"N">
 is uniquely determined modulo <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/im=
ages/equations/ChineseRemainderTheorem/Inline7.svg" class=3D"inlineformula"=
 style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"18" height=
=3D"21" alt=3D"rs">. An equivalent statement is that if <img src=3D"https:/=
/mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/ChineseRemainderTheorem/Inline8.svg=
" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"64" height=3D"21" alt=3D"(r,s)=3D1">, then every pair of <a=
 href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ResidueClass.html">residue
 classes</a> modulo <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equati=
ons/ChineseRemainderTheorem/Inline9.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"m=
ax-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"7" height=3D"21" alt=
=3D"r"> and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Chin=
eseRemainderTheorem/Inline10.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-heig=
ht:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"7" height=3D"21" alt=3D"s"> c=
orresponds to a simple <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ResidueClas=
s.html">residue
 class</a> modulo <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equation=
s/ChineseRemainderTheorem/Inline11.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"ma=
x-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"18" height=3D"21" alt=
=3D"rs">.
</p>
<p>
The Chinese remainder theorem is implemented in the <a href=3D"http://www.w=
olfram.com/language/">Wolfram Language</a> as <tt><a href=3D"http://referen=
ce.wolfram.com/language/ref/ChineseRemainder.html">ChineseRemainder</a></tt=
>[<img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/ChineseRemaind=
erTheorem/Inline12.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;ma=
